node.text: Today we went to see Calypso‚Äôs Cave in Gozo. Unfortunately it‚Äôs closed for tourists now but we still had a glimpse of the entrance at least. According to the local myth this is the place where Calypso (One of Oceanides sea nymphs, the daughter of the Titan god Atlas and Tethys.) kept Odysseus from returning to Ithaca after the Trojan war. Calypso saved Odysseus from the sea when he was adrift for 9 days after losing his ship. She welcomed him and fell in love with him. She wanted him to be her immortal husband by giving him eternal youth. Odysseus didn‚Äôt accept it because he was still dreaming about going back home to Ithaca and his wife. Calypso was so much in love with him that despite his wishes she hoped he would fall in love with her and kept seducing him. Eventually she succeeded and made him her lover. They stayed together in Calypsos‚Äô beautiful cave home for 7 years before the gods intervened and  convinced her to let Odysseus go. She helped him to build a boat to take him home.
